<font color="#FF0000">A BROTHER STUMBLES</font><br>
<tt>Wed Aug 20 23:08:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Mustang Two Four,<br><br>
Silent Warrior reads your call.  Holding high and dry.  Maintaining you cover.  Find a safe zone and set it down.  If necessary we will bring in the Sandies and lay down some suppression.<br><br>
You carry your burden well.  I find the wisdom of your fore fathers a great strength for me.  You have given me this and I will be forever greatful.<br><br>
We are never prisoners of the past.  Honor your past when it  when it gives to you that which you need the most.  Hold to your beliefs because they create that which we are.<br><br>
When a Warrior stumbles under a burden too heavy to carry his brothers are there to lift him up.<br><br>
Ride my pony for a while.  I would be honored.
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


